{"author":{"id":"1949ffc23f11a8cb4f8c42a45c9ad241b49570df9a18687489e9ea78d87c54a3"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772048171,"nonce":"tCE2rGr/qkcj1Mp1SY7YeAb+d8I=","title":"Integrate Treescope for interactive model visualization","message":"[Imported from GitHub #39] (created 2026-01-26T15:56:15Z)\n\n## Motivation\n\nFeedbax models—especially `Graph` instances with nested `Component` trees—are complex PyTree structures that are difficult to inspect with standard `repr()` output. As models grow in complexity (multiple feedback loops, intervention nodes, nested mechanics), debugging and understanding model structure becomes increasingly challenging.\n\n[Treescope](https://github.com/google-deepmind/treescope) is a standalone interactive HTML pretty-printer designed specifically for this problem. Originally part of Penzai, it's now available as an independent package that works directly with Equinox models.\n\n## Proposal\n\nAdd optional Treescope integration for notebook environments.\n\n### Minimal integration\n\n```python\n# feedbax/_treescope.py or similar\ndef setup_treescope(autovisualize_arrays: bool = True):\n    \"\"\"Configure Treescope as the default IPython renderer.\"\"\"\n    import treescope\n    treescope.basic_interactive_setup(autovisualize_arrays=autovisualize_arrays)\n```\n\n### Extended integration\n\n- Custom renderers for Feedbax-specific types (`Graph`, `Wire`, `Component`)\n- State visualization helpers (render `State` alongside model structure)\n- Integration with existing `plot` module for array visualization preferences\n\n## Features Treescope provides\n\n- **Expandable/collapsible subtrees** - navigate deep nesting interactively\n- **N-dimensional array visualization** - embedded tensor heatmaps\n- **Color-coding** - distinguish component types visually\n- **Copy path buttons** - click to copy keypath for any node\n- **Roundtrip mode** (press `r`) - shows fully-qualified type names\n- **Works with Equinox** - no framework migration needed\n\n## Relation to #18\n\nThis addresses #18 (\"Pretty printing of inputs and outputs of model stages\") more comprehensively than a custom solution would, since Treescope handles arbitrary PyTrees including arrays.\n\n## Dependencies\n\n```\ntreescope  # standalone package, ~minimal dependencies\n```\n\n## References\n\n- [Treescope documentation](https://treescope.readthedocs.io/)\n- [Treescope GitHub](https://github.com/google-deepmind/treescope)\n- [ICML 2024 MechInterp Workshop paper](https://arxiv.org/html/2408.00211v1)\n\n---\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.5 \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e","files":null}]}